reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 5 months in and no issues at all
reviews.reviewText: Looks great overall I have not had any problems with it. It is very easy to use and change colors and it comes with many different features as far as what you can do with the color modes. I don't think it comes with any software to control lighting but I myself usually keep it on a color that matches my setup and the light blue color is amazing. not to mention that this keyboard is quieter than some other red switch keyboard's I've had. It looks amazing and the color has not faded or anything and I use it heavily on a daily basis

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great, "quiet thock" and nearly-fully programmable RGB lights
reviews.reviewText: This is a great keyboard. Not only is it super cute and an amazing price, but it is one of the few companies that I've seen say you can set custom settings and really mean it. I will say its a pretty clicky keyboard as far as red switches tend to go, but for me this is a big plus. If you are thinking of avoiding the board because you think it will be totally silent, that is not the case! Plus, for 40 bucks, you can't get a better value.

reviews.reviewText: My son bought this and he simply loves it. The price, the value and the light up keyboard that you can program goes with all of his decor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice keyboard but missing arrow key function
reviews.reviewText: This is my first 60% keyboard so I only deducted 1 star.It’s a beautiful and nice keyboard. Love the design and backlit colors. I haven’t done a lot of typing with this and it need a little adjustment to type on this if you switch from MacBook keyboard.I really need the arrows keys to move around. Fn + i j k l won’t always work. I’m able to use it a few time in UEFI BIOS (Asrock), won’t work in Chrome/Edge, I’m on Windows11 FYI.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love this keyboard so very much. It's the perfect size, with beautiful colors and key caps. The switches have the perfect feel and sound, and the RGB is really stunning. There are also so many options to choose from in the lighting. It's everything I wanted in a keyboard and I couldn't be happier!

reviews.reviewTitle: It's beyond better than what I thought...
reviews.reviewText: This keyboard is the best looking keyboard you can find today with dozens of extra key caps which come with 2 key cap removers. The RGB is way better than I expected, and so is the sound. It has over 10 different RGB changing themes and you can make yourself a custom RGB theme on its app. This is just an amazing keyboard overall, worth every penny, and better than every Razer keyboards out there which cost 2-3x more. There are however a few comments that aren't happy with it because it doesn't work and so on but those are most likely just faulty ones with issues so don't get scared by those comments and buy it, i definitely recommend it.
